# Static analysis & verification tooling — exact commands, versions, raw output

Working directory: `/home/darkfriend/projects/antigravity/ajuna-tokenswap`
Date of run: 2026-04-26
Commit at audit time: `5b13a8b feat(security): close out REVIEW_v2 findings (MED-1, MED-2, LOW-1, INFO-1/3/4/5)` (clean tree).

## 1. Solidity compiler (sanity)

```
$ npx hardhat compile
Nothing to compile / Successfully compiled 48 Solidity files
```

`hardhat.config.ts` was edited during the audit to add `outputSelection['*']['*'] = ['storageLayout']` so that the OZ upgrades-core plugin and the storage-map dump can read storageLayout from the build-info JSON. The original setting (no storageLayout) silently yielded an OZ plugin error, which is itself worth flagging — fresh repos cannot validate upgrade safety until the operator adds this output selection.

