## 3. OpenZeppelin upgrades-core validate

`@openzeppelin/upgrades-core@1.50.x` (latest at audit time, fetched via `npx --yes`).

```
$ npx --yes @openzeppelin/upgrades-core validate artifacts/build-info
Note: Reinitializers are not included in validations by default
    contracts/mocks/AjunaERC20V2.sol:16: If you want to validate this function as an initializer, annotate it with '@custom:oz-upgrades-validate-as-initializer'
Note: Reinitializers are not included in validations by default
    contracts/mocks/AjunaWrapperV2.sol:16: If you want to validate this function as an initializer, annotate it with '@custom:oz-upgrades-validate-as-initializer'

 ✔  contracts/AjunaERC20.sol:AjunaERC20

 ✘  contracts/AjunaWrapper.sol:AjunaWrapper
      @openzeppelin/contracts/utils/ReentrancyGuard.sol:58: Contract `ReentrancyGuard` has a constructor
          Define an initializer instead
          https://zpl.in/upgrades/error-001

 ✔  contracts/mocks/AjunaERC20V2.sol:AjunaERC20V2

 ✘  contracts/mocks/AjunaWrapperV2.sol:AjunaWrapperV2
      @openzeppelin/contracts/utils/ReentrancyGuard.sol:58: Contract `ReentrancyGuard` has a constructor
          Define an initializer instead
          https://zpl.in/upgrades/error-001

FAILED (4 upgradeable contracts detected, 2 passed, 2 failed)
```

This output is the basis of finding ATS-09. The plugin would refuse to deploy or upgrade `AjunaWrapper` without an `@custom:oz-upgrades-unsafe-allow` annotation in the inheritance, because the parent `ReentrancyGuard` (non-upgradeable v5.5+) has a constructor that runs only on the implementation. Behavior on the proxy is currently safe by accident (proxy storage at the namespaced slot starts at 0, which is not equal to `ENTERED == 2`), but the plugin's gate is correct — using `ReentrancyGuardUpgradeable` would remove the warning entirely.

## 4. Slither (static analyzer)

`slither-analyzer 0.11.5`, installed via `pip --user` and run with `env -i HOME=$HOME PATH=…` to bypass an unrelated `solc-select` configuration issue (`/usr/.solc-select` was not writable on this host).

Default detectors:

```
$ slither . --filter-paths "node_modules|contracts/mocks" --foundry-out-directory artifacts
'npx hardhat clean' / 'compile --force' running
INFO:Detectors:
Detector: incorrect-equality
AjunaWrapper.isInvariantHealthy() (contracts/AjunaWrapper.sol#228-230) uses a dangerous strict equality:
    - token.totalSupply() == foreignAsset.balanceOf(address(this))
INFO:Detectors:
Detector: naming-convention
Variable AjunaERC20.__gap (contracts/AjunaERC20.sol#107) is not in mixedCase
Parameter AjunaWrapper.initialize(address,address)._token (contracts/AjunaWrapper.sol#75) is not in mixedCase
Parameter AjunaWrapper.initialize(address,address)._foreignAssetPrecompile (contracts/AjunaWrapper.sol#76) is not in mixedCase
Variable AjunaWrapper.__gap (contracts/AjunaWrapper.sol#296) is not in mixedCase
INFO:Slither:. analyzed (45 contracts with 101 detectors), 5 result(s) found
```

All-detectors run additionally surfaced low-level-call and missing-zero-check on `contracts/mocks/ReentrantToken.sol`, which is intentional in a mock and not in scope.

The single substantive output — `incorrect-equality` on `isInvariantHealthy` — is intentional: the function is documented as a strict-equality health probe whose `false` return is an alarm signal for off-chain monitors. The function name conflates over- and under-collateralization (ATS-12 INFO).

