## 5. Storage-layout dump (raw solc output)

`solc 0.8.30` via `node_modules/solc`. Manual driver script (kept ephemeral) requested `outputSelection.storageLayout` and printed slot/offset/type for every linearized variable in the production contracts. Results documented in `audit/storage-layout.md`.

```
══ contracts/AjunaWrapper.sol:AjunaWrapper ══
  slot 0 off 0  size 20  token         (t_contract(AjunaERC20)8622)
  slot 1 off 0  size 20  foreignAsset  (t_contract(IERC20Precompile)9229)
  slot 1 off 20 size 1   allowlistEnabled (t_bool)
  slot 2 off 0  size 32  allowlisted   (t_mapping(t_address,t_bool))
  slot 3 off 0  size 1472 __gap        (t_array(t_uint256)46_storage)

══ contracts/AjunaERC20.sol:AjunaERC20 ══
  slot 0 off 0  size 1   _tokenDecimals (t_uint8)
  slot 1 off 0  size 1568 __gap         (t_array(t_uint256)49_storage)
```

This is the basis for ATS-05, ATS-06.

## 6. Unavailable / not-attempted tools

- **Aderyn** — not installed and no offline binary available on the audit host. A manual review covered the same ground (immutables, missing-event-emission, dead code) without finding additional issues.
- **Mythril** — not attempted; symbolic-execution coverage on this small surface would not surpass slither + manual review for the time budget.
- **Echidna / Foundry invariant fuzzing** — not attempted. The invariant under test (`totalSupply == balanceOf(wrapper)`) is exercised by every assertion in `wrapper.test.ts` (`checkInvariant` called after every state-changing op) and by the targeted PoCs in `test/audit/`. A property-based fuzz job would harden coverage; recommended in the report under "Test-suite assessment".
- **Hardhat-upgrades validateUpgrade** — superseded by the standalone OZ upgrades-core run above; same engine.

## 7. Manual review pass count

- `contracts/AjunaWrapper.sol` — 3 reads end-to-end; line-by-line for deposit/withdraw/initialize/_authorizeUpgrade.
- `contracts/AjunaERC20.sol` — 2 reads end-to-end; line-by-line for initialize/burnFrom/_authorizeUpgrade.
- `contracts/mocks/*` — 1 read each, focused on whether mocks could shadow real semantics.
- `scripts/deploy_*` and `docs/PRODUCTION-CHECKLIST.md` — cross-checked against the contract code; ATS-01 surfaced from this delta.
- `docs/SECURITY.md`, `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`, `docs/UPGRADE.md` — read in full; spec-mismatch findings (ATS-02, ATS-06) come from these.
